HEADWORD: Monadelphia
<hw>Mon`a*del"phi*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
from Gr. <grk>mo`nos</grk> alone + <grk>'adelfo`s</grk> brother.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A Linnaean class of plants having the stamens
united into a tube, or ring, by the filaments, as in the Mallow
family.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monadelphous</ent>⟦br⟧
